This directory shows that you can create nice looking anti-aliased images from
pinto images.

Save your image at double size in pinto, then use the pintoImageDownsize()
function to create a half-size anti-aliased image. The double size pinto image
is still much smaller than the normal size anti-aliased image.

Also see the pintoToRgba utility's "rbgaDownsize" argument in
source/utilities/pintoToRgba.

Name                           Size
----                           ----
Z_32x32.pinto                  17
Z_16x16_antialiased.png        109

heart_32x32.pinto              64
heart_16x16_antialiased.png    188

